The paper deals with machine learning approaches for answering visual-relational queries in web-extracted knowledge graphs. The use of convolutional networks and knowledge graph embedding methods to answer such queries suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also deals with multi-relational image retrieval and zero-shot learning scenarios, which suggest that it could also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
